# Supabase SQL and RLS Rules

- Every table that stores agency-linked data must include RLS policy coverage.
- Policies must enforce agency-level isolation for read and write operations.
- Prefer explicit policy names and migration-safe SQL with reversible intent.
- Keep schema changes aligned with lifecycle states used in product flows.
- Add indexes for high-frequency lookups in checklist, deliverable, and audit queries.
